RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 58. Claiming Purse 14500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of Three Races Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (W V A Races Not Considered In El igibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIDNIGHT FLING gave early chase outside, rounded the turn in the four and five paths, dug in for the lead mid-stretch and finished under steady handling. AT THE HALF chased through the backstretch, raced in the four path of the turn, eased outward nearing the head of the lane and dueled through later yards for second. K K CAN exchanged contact with Christine's Cosmo leaving the gate, picked up the chase inside then outfinished in the later duel for second. MI YAYIS chased through the backstretch, raced near the rail on the turn and ran evenly to mid-stretch before flattening stride. BALLYMENA gave chase, raced off the rail on the turn then flattened inside the sixteenth pole. CHRISTINE'S COSMO bobbled and exchanged contact with K K Can leaving the gate, picked up the chase through the backstretch, angled out leaving the turn and finished well outside. LADY LICIOUS gave chase though never factored. SHANIA SEA set a clear early pace but shortened stride near the rail on the turn. RIDE ON BEAUTY gave chase through the backstretch then flattened in the three path of the turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Shania Sea
ENTRY.OWNER: Two Ten Twelve Triple T Racing

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 59. Claiming Purse 13300. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 16 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AIR MEDAL saved ground on the first turn, started a bid leaving the three eighths pole and raced near the rail most of the far turn, angled to the outside into the lane and steadily improved to get up the final yards. FELICIAS CASTLE rounded the first turn in the five path and left the turn outside, bid nearing the three eighths pole, closed ground in the five path on the far turn and took a slim lead mid-stretch, but was caught in the final yards. MACHEN'S RIDGE bobbled at the break but rated close in the three path, gave chase from the three eighths pole, raced three wide on the far turn then outfinished in the duel through the stretch. BERNIE THE GAMBLER saved early ground, bid nearing the three eighths pole, raced in the three and four paths of the far turn and ran evenly in the lane. MIO GRACELAND rated a short lead inside, came under pressure leaving the half mile pole and kept the edge at the rail on the far turn, but was met mid-stretch and weakened the final sixteenth. WINDSOR'S TRACKER rated close inside on the first turn, gave chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, raced near the rail on the far turn and weakened the final sixteenth. MADDEYE MOODY rated close off the rail on the first turn, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail and weakened in the lane. ROCKET J. raced off the rail on the first turn and showed little response through the backstretch. YDOUHAVETOBESOMEAN gave chase from the half mile pole but showed little response. MEGALODON'SREVENGE stalked the earlier pace from the three and four paths, challenged into the backstretch but dropped back at the five sixteenths pole and weakened on the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Windsor's Tracker
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W

ENTRY.NAME: Mio Graceland
ENTRY.OWNER: A and B Racing Stable LLC

ENTRY.NAME: Air Medal
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,bid 3/8,rail far turn,angled out 1/8,up final yards

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHASENJOHNATHAN settled off the early pace, started a bid leaving the three eighths pole and closed toward contention on the turn, left the turn five wide, dug in for the lead later yards and raced clear nearing the wire. B. J. MOOSE came away awkwardly then hustled to the front leaving the half mile pole and set a pressured pace, rounded the turn at the rail, dug in under steady handling but relented later yards. HARLEY SIOUX chased inside, rounded the turn at the rail and ran evenly in the lane. LIEUTENANT BROWN came away a step slow and gave distant early chase, rounded the turn in the three path and finished well. TURTLE DOVE chased toward the inside, raced near the rail on the turn, left the turn five wide then steadied and altered course to the outside mid-stretch. OFFICER STONE gave chase, raced in the four path of the turn then flattened inside the sixteenth pole. NEEDNOEXPLANATION gave chase, raced close off the rail on the turn and weakened. MEETMARYSMAN gave chase outside, rounded the turn in the four and five paths and showed little in the lane.

ENTRY.OWNER: Straughn William E and Thacker Daniel

ENTRY.OWNER: CM Racing and Jones Jr Michael E

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 67. Claiming Purse 13300. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LION OF THE SEA was bumped outward and into Charitably Gifted leaving the gate then gave chase, raced near the rail on the turn, angled to the four path toward the head of the lane, dug in for the lead mid-stretch and dueled clear later yards. I ONCE STOOD ALONE ducked outward and into Lion Of The Sea leaving the gate then gave chase, raced near the rail on the turn and dug in to take second later yards. CHARITABLY GIFTED was bumped off stride leaving the gate, gave chase through the backstretch, rounded the turn in the three and four paths then relented second later yards. FIT BUT FAT was hustled to the front inside approaching the five sixteenths pole, dug in at even terms nearest the rail midway on the turn then flattened stride inside the sixteenth pole. WARRIOR'S ESTATE chased the pace outside, rounded the turn about the five path, steadied off the heels of Lion Of The Sea leaving the turn and was kept in hand through the stretch. ROLL DEM BONES became anxious in the gate then gave chase, rounded the turn about the four path and flattened in the lane. SAAFEN steadied early and gave only distant chase, race off the rail into the turn, angled widest leaving the turn and showed little in the lane. HOPE HE'S FAST gave chase but was shuffled back toward the quarter pole. HE'S ON THE LINE set the early pace, gave chase nearing the five sixteenths pole then weakened toward the head of the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Fit But Fat
ENTRY.COMMENT: hustled up near 5/16,met rail mid turn,flattened 1/16

ENTRY.OWNER: Brooks Gerald E and Hess Jr Carl L

ENTRY.OWNER: Shepherd Robert Phillips Jason and Harrison Glenn N

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 7F Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Special Weight Purse 32700. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 116 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LAUGHINTOTHEBANK came away a bit awkwardly and settled close in the three and four paths, challenged toward the three eighths pole, took over two deep at the quarter, drew clear midway on the far turn and was steadily handled in the lane. S S FRONTIER ANGEL saved early ground, bid nearing the three eighths pole and raced near the rail most of the far turn, angled to the four path approaching the head of the lane and finished well. LADY GANGSTER rated close inside on the opening turn, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced in the three path of the far turn, was carried out toward the head of the lane and came along for third late. PHANTOM QUEEN tapered in and set the early pace, came under pressure toward the three eighths pole, was met at the rail approaching the quarter, dropped back midway on the far turn and weakened in the lane. NINETY PROOF settled off the early pace in the three and four paths, picked up the chase approaching the three eighths pole, was met at the rail nearing the quarter, dropped back midway on the turn and weakened in the lane. A GIRL HAS A NAME raced well off the pace about the three path the first turn and showed little response. SHY BELLA rated close in the three path the first turn but fell nearing the half mile pole and had to be euthanized on the track. The Stewards reviewed the incident at the half mile pole before declaring this race official.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 70. Claiming Purse 19400. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, For Each $1,000 To $8,000 1 lb. (W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility)(Races Whe re Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STORMIN ROCKET rated close inside on the first turn, eased out with a bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, took over three wide midway on the far turn and was kept alert through the stretch. FEARNOUGHT rated close off the rail the first turn, picked up the chase into the backstretch and raced near the rail on the far turn, eased out leaving the turn and dug in to take second late. BUBBA G stalked the earlier pace from the three path, challenged toward the three eighths pole but dropped back at the quarter pole, raced at the rail on the turn and dueled for third. COUNTRY CHARLIE was bumped leaving the gate then saved ground, picked up the chase toward the three eighths pole, raced near the rail on the far turn and ran evenly in the lane. FULL AHEAD took over while tapering to the inside and rated the pace, came under pressure nearing the three eighths pole, dueled clear of Bubba G but was met midway on the far turn and weakened in the lane. EISELE ducked in and made contact with Country Charlie leaving the gate then saved ground close to the early pace, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but flattened at the rail on the far turn. SIMILAR TASTE showed little response through the backstretch. LOOKA LOOKA bobbled at the break and dropped well back.

ENTRY.NAME: Country Charlie
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped break,saved ground,chased 3/8,rail far turn,evenly lane

ENTRY.NAME: Stormin Rocket
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated close,eased out,bid 7/16,up 3wd mid turn,kept alert lane

ENTRY.NAME: Bubba G
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 62. Maiden Claiming Purse 20600. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: YAZZERA (PER) took the lead nearing the three quarter pole and angled to the rail to rate the pace, came under pressure at the three eighths pole, widened at the rail on the far turn and was steadily handled in the lane. SUPER SWEETIE saved ground off the pace on the opening turn, bid into the backstretch, rounded the far turn in the four path and dueled clear in second inside the sixteenth pole. SWEET FACTOR stalked from the four path the first turn, bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole and rounded the far turn about the three path, then flattened stride the final sixteenth. TAKE CHARGE LISA rated close to the early pace inside, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and weakened in the lane. COWGIRL HOP was never a factor. SUPER WICKED stalked in the three path then faded through the backstretch. PUERTORICAN DIVA saved ground. BREEZY CONNECTION was taken up on the first turn and walked off post race.

ENTRY.OWNER: Iyacyas Racing LLC and Delgado William

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 7F Dirt CR: 88. Allowance Purse 35100. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of Three Races Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since January 16 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUNGLE BEAST raced in the three path the first turn, started a three wide bid approaching the three eighths pole and took the lead two deep at the quarter, rounded the far turn off the rail and was steadily handled in the lane. SUE LOVES BARBADOS raced off the rail on the opening turn, bid nearing the three eighths pole and took the lead toward the five sixteenths, but was caught into the far turn, steadied at the rail approaching the head of the lane, angled out at the eighth pole and just lasted for second. BO'S BOURBON angled in and rated the pace, came under pressure nearing the three eighths pole and was met past the pole, dropped back leaving the five sixteenths but came back in the stretch and just missed second. OROCOVIX raced well off the pace in the two and three paths, bid passing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and passed some rivals in the lane. BAAGY was bumped at the break and settled off the rail on the first turn, picked up the chase leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and weakened. TARAASHOQ was never a factor. MOTAWAAFEQ saved ground off the pace, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole but faded approaching the far turn. LIKE SEGAL came away awkwardly and made contact with Baagy, rounded the first turn in the four path, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole then faded on the far turn. After a Stewards inquiry and subsequent claim of foul against the rider of Jungle Beast for alleged interference nearing the eighth pole, lodged by the rider of Sue Loves Barbados, no change was warranted.

ENTRY.NAME: Baagy
ENTRY.OWNER: Pesaturo Gus and Joy Kevin J

ENTRY.NAME: Bo's Bourbon
ENTRY.OWNER: Metz Larry and Bone Robert D

ENTRY.NAME: Orocovix
ENTRY.COMMENT: well off pace,2& 3p,bid 3/8,3p far turn,passed rivals

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 9 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 15700. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE SEPTEMBER 16, 2022. Weight, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since September 16 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Con sidered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FU MAN SUE was squeezed at the break then gave chase, rounded the turn about the three path, dug in for the lead nearing mid-stretch and edged clear inside the sixteenth pole. BE BE BOP chased, raced off the rail on the turn, dueled through the stretch and held on for second. WIDGET FACTORY exchanged contact with Doesn't Make Cents leaving the gate, picked up the chase through the backstretch, rounded the turn near the rail and dug in to take third later yards. BULL SHARK set a pressured pace, rounded the turn near the rail but was met while flattening stride mid-stretch. NO FOOLING DUDE broke in and made contact with Fu Man Sue, gave chase through the backstretch, raced off the rail on the turn and ran evenly in the lane. DOESN'T MAKE CENTS exchanged contact with Widget Factory leaving the gate then gave chase inside, raced near the rail on the turn and showed little in the lane. SHACKLEFORDS STORM engaged in close early chase, raced in the four path of the turn and weakened in the lane. SHACKLED broke outward and made contact with Fu Man Sue and was not a factor. BARNSTORM was never a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Fu Man Sue
ENTRY.COMMENT: squeezed break,chased,3p turn,up near 1/16,clear later yards

ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Ronney W and Conrad Randall R
